# Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## 1. Product Overview

**Product Name:** Mobile Shop E‑Commerce Website
**Purpose:** Build an online platform for selling mobile phones, accessories, and related services (repairs, warranty, exchanges) for a local or national mobile shop.

The platform should allow customers to browse products, compare phones, place orders, and track deliveries, while enabling shop owners to manage inventory, pricing, and promotions efficiently.

---

## 2. Goals & Objectives

### Business Goals

* Increase mobile phone and accessory sales
* Reach customers beyond physical store location
* Reduce manual inventory & order handling
* Enable frequent discounts & flash sales

### User Goals

* Easily find and compare mobile phones
* Trust product authenticity and warranty
* Simple checkout and fast delivery
* Clear stock availability and pricing

---

## 3. Target Users

### Primary Users

* Customers looking to buy smartphones online
* Customers buying accessories (cases, chargers, earbuds)

### Secondary Users

* Shop Owner / Admin
* Inventory Manager
* Delivery Partner (optional)

---

## 4. User Roles & Permissions

### Customer

* Browse products
* Search & filter phones
* Add to cart & wishlist
* Place orders
* Track order status
* View order history

### Admin (Shop Owner)

* Add / edit / delete products
* Manage stock quantity
* Set prices & discounts
* Manage orders
* Update order status
* View sales analytics

### Staff (Optional)

* Update stock
* Update order status

---

## 5. Core Features

### 5.1 Product Catalog

* Categories:

  * Smartphones
  * Accessories
  * Refurbished Phones
* Product Details:

  * Brand, Model
  * Price & Discount
  * Specifications (RAM, Storage, Camera, Battery)
  * Images (multiple)
  * Stock availability
  * Warranty info

### 5.2 Search & Filters

* Search by name or brand
* Filters:

  * Price range
  * Brand
  * RAM / Storage
  * Availability (In Stock)

### 5.3 Cart & Checkout

* Add/remove items
* Update quantity
* Coupon code support
* Checkout flow:

  * Login / Guest checkout
  * Address selection
  * Payment method selection

### 5.4 Payment System

* Cash on Delivery (mandatory)
* Online payment (optional):

  * eSewa / Khalti / Stripe

### 5.5 Order Management

* Order status:

  * Pending
  * Confirmed
  * Shipped
  * Delivered
  * Cancelled
* Email / SMS notifications (optional)

### 5.6 Inventory Management

* Stock count per product
* Auto stock reduction after purchase
* Out‑of‑stock handling
* Low stock alerts for admin

### 5.7 Discounts & Offers

* Product‑level discounts
* Category‑level discounts
* Flash sales (time‑based)
* Coupon codes

### 5.8 User Accounts

* Login / Signup
* Profile management
* Address book
* Order history

---

## 6. Admin Panel Requirements

* Dashboard:

  * Total sales
  * Total orders
  * Low stock items
* Product management
* Order management
* Discount management
* User management

---

## 7. Non‑Functional Requirements

### Performance

* Page load time < 3 seconds
* Optimized images

### Security

* Secure authentication
* Role‑based access control
* Encrypted payments

### Scalability

* Support up to 10,000+ products
* Handle sale spikes during discounts

### SEO

* SEO‑friendly URLs
* Meta tags for products
* Sitemap support

---

## 8. Tech Stack (Suggested)

### Frontend

* React (or Next.js)
* Tailwind / Bootstrap

### Backend

* Supabase / Django / FastAPI

### Database

* PostgreSQL

### Hosting

* Vercel / Netlify (Frontend)
* Supabase / VPS (Backend)

---

## 9. Future Enhancements

* Product comparison feature
* EMI / installment payments
* AI‑based phone recommendation
* Customer reviews & ratings
* Mobile app (React Native)

---

## 10. Success Metrics

* Conversion rate
* Average order value
* Monthly active users
* Inventory turnover rate

---

## 11. Assumptions & Constraints

* Initial focus on local market
* Limited delivery coverage at launch
* Manual verification of orders initially

---

**End of PRD**
